    "SUNDAY MARCH 21 1937 Leon Blum on Stalin Stalins Machine Of Terror hlllllllllllllllllllIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIllllllllllllls By LEON BLUM Premier ot France In an Article Written for his Newspaper Le Populaire in 1931 Shortly After the Fa mous Menshevik Trial in Russia and B ore he Became Head of the French Govermn nent HERE are accusations T which are at once 8o odious and so absurd that one feels a sort of shame at the mere idea of having to defend omeself against them According to Stalin and the OGPU the Menshevik Party is supposed to have undertaken the direction of a vast internal plot aiming at the systematic sabotage of the activity of the Soviet institutions and the restora tion of capitalism in Russia It is moreover supposed to have attempted to in fluence public opinion and the Governments with a view to armed intervention against Soviet Russia e e e Disguise Failures In this double action it is sup posed to have followed the di rections of the Second Interna tional and to have benefited by its political and even financial support Hilferding Kautsky and Vandervelde like myself are particularly mentioned among the principal defend ants Consider the circumstances the court"
